org.openimaj.image.processing.convolution.filterbank

Class FilterBank

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.image.processing.convolution.filterbank.FilterBank
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImageAnalyser<FImage>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LawsTextureBase, LeungMalikFilterBank, RootFilterSetFilterBank, SchmidFilterBank

    public abstract class FilterBank
extends Object
implements ImageAnalyser<FImage>
    A FilterBank is a set of convolution filters which can be applied to an image. The filterbank allows a response vector of the filter at each pixel in the image to be generated. Convolution is performed in the fourier domain for efficiency (the fft's of the filters are cached, and the fft of the image only has to be performed once for all convolutions)
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
